        <h2>Community & Advocacy Partners</h2>
        <p>Praxis Initiative anchors the Arizona Justice Reform Coalition (AJRC), a table of organizations including ACLU of Arizona, Mass Liberation AZ, Arizona Faith Network, and the NAACP Maricopa County Branch. Together, we coordinate legislative strategy, share resources, and ensure directly impacted voices lead every campaign. In 2025, AJRC pooled resources to support SB 1507, amplifying our collective power at the Capitol. Our <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> program coordinates AJRC's legislative priorities.</p>
        <p>Our <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> program partners with Sonoran Prevention Works, Shot in the Dark, and Indigenous Roots Phoenix to provide peer-led harm reduction. These partnerships enable us to distribute 5,000+ naloxone kits annually and respond to overdose clusters within hours. We co-sponsor "Surviving Overdose" support groups for family members, led by bilingual staff.</p>
        <p>Indigenous justice is central to our work. We partner with Native-led organizations like Indigenous Peoples Justice and the Navajo Nation Human Rights Commission to address Native over-incarceration. Native people are 5.3% of Arizona's population but 13% of ADCRR custody. Our joint campaigns focus on tribal jurisdiction, cultural programming inside prisons, and post-release reconnection to tribal communities.</p>
