        <h2>Cultural & Institutional Partners</h2>
        <p>Our <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> program thrives through collaboration with Phoenix Art Museum, Arizona Humanities, and the Poetry Center at University of Arizona. These partnerships bring professional artists into facilities and exhibit incarcerated work publicly. The "Perryville Poetry Project" was co-published with University of Arizona Press, giving statewide bookstore distribution. We're planning a 2026 exhibition, "Visions from Inside," featuring visual artists at ASU Art Museum.</p>
        <p>Academic partnerships strengthen our credibility. We work with Arizona State University's School of Criminology to evaluate outcomes and Northern Arizona University to track recidivism among <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training</strong> graduates. These data partnerships ensure our work is evidence-based and impact is measurable.</p>
        <p>Faith communities provide essential support. We partner with Tempe First United Methodist, St. Mary's Basilica, and Islamic Center of North Phoenix to host reentry supply drives, provide meeting space, and mobilize congregants for legislative action. Their moral voice amplifies our policy demands.</p>
